#: ../../S/Suzie-COBOL.rst:10
msgid ""
"[IBM: prob. : from Frank Zappa's ‘Suzy Creamcheese’] n. A coder straight out"
" of training school who knows everything except the value of comments in "
"plain English. Also (fashionable among personkind wishing to avoid "
"accusations of sexism) ‘Sammy Cobol’ or (in some non-IBM circles) ‘Cobol "
"Charlie’."
msgstr ""
"[IBM: おそらく : Frank Zappaの‘Suzy Creamcheese’から] 名詞 "
"平易な英語によるコメントの価値以外はすべて知っている、訓練校を出たての "
"programmer。また(性差別の非難を避けたい人々の間で流行りの)‘Sammy Cobol’や、(一部の非IBMの界隈で)‘Cobol "
"Charlie’とも。"

#: ../../S/Suzie-COBOL.rst:15
msgid ""
"[proposed] Meta-name for any :ref:`code-grinder`\\, analogous to :ref:`J--"
"Random-Hacker`\\."
msgstr "[提案] あらゆる\\ :ref:`code-grinder`\\ のメタ名。\\ :ref:`J--Random-Hacker`\\ に類似。"
